messages.title: Don't forget to....
messages.content: Use Your Postal Vote. Britain has started growing again but there's much more to do. Let's stay on the road to a stronger economy and a more secure future for you, your family and for South Norfolk. Casting a protest vote could cost you dear. If you forget to return a postal vote you can take it to any polling station in South Norfolk before 10pm on May 7th and your vote will be counted.

keyPolicies.policyDescription: We aim to freeze your Council Tax for another 4 years.
We’ll grow the economy by investing in better facilities that benefit residents and businesses.
We’ll get superfast Broadband to every neighbourhood.
We’ll protect our environment and keep South Norfolk clean & tidy.
We’ll help those most in need to stay safe and independent at home.
